# Security Standards

## Authentication

- Access token: JWT RS256, **15-minute expiry**
- Refresh token: opaque string, `httpOnly` cookie, **7-day expiry**, stored in DB
- Refresh Token Rotation: issue a new refresh token on every use; revoke the old one
- Revoked tokens: blacklisted in Redis with TTL = remaining token lifetime

## Multitenancy (mandatory on every request)

- Extract `tenantId` from JWT in `tenant.middleware.ts`
- Reject any authenticated request without valid `tenantId` with `401`
- All DB queries filtered by `tenantId` — enforced by repository method signatures
- Cache keys prefixed: `tenant:{tenantId}:*`
- BullMQ jobs include `tenantId` in payload
- Every log line includes `tenantId` as a structured field

## RBAC

Roles: `SUPER_ADMIN | TENANT_ADMIN | MANAGER | OPERATOR | VIEWER`

```typescript
// ✅ Check permission, not role
fastify.authorize(['orders:cancel'])

// ❌ Never check role directly in routes
if (user.role === 'MANAGER') { ... }
```

Permissions are `{ resource: string, action: string }` pairs.

## Passwords

- Hash with **Argon2id** (`argon2` library)
- Never log passwords — not even in debug level

## HTTP Security Headers (apply globally)

```
helmet                   → security headers
@fastify/rate-limit      → per-IP and per-user rate limiting
@fastify/csrf-protection → CSRF for cookie routes
cors                     → origin whitelist, never wildcard in production
```

## Forbidden

- Wildcard CORS in production
- Storing plain-text passwords or tokens
- Logging sensitive fields (password, token, creditCard)
- Queries without `tenantId` filter
- Physical record deletion
